  "description": "After a Shadowing attempt on the Pronunciation page, the result screen lists every missed/partial word but offers no fast way to actually *practice* them — users have to navigate away and pick a new sentence. Add a frontend-only 'Drill Missed Words 🎯' panel/CTA on the shadowing result view that cycles the user through each non-correct word from `feedback.word_feedback` (excluding `is_correct === true`) one-by-one. For each word: (1) auto-play the word in isolation via `tts.speak(word)`, (2) play it inside a short example phrase ('Say: <word>. <word> is …'), (3) auto-start `useSpeechRecognition` and compare the recognized transcript (lowercased, punctuation-stripped) against the target word — case-insensitive exact match counts as ✓, otherwise show 'heard: \"…\"' with a Try Again button (max 3 attempts per word, then Skip). Show a small progress strip (e.g. 'Word 2 / 4 ✓✓·○'). On finish, show a summary card ('You nailed 3 of 4 — Retry whole sentence?') with two buttons: 'Retry sentence' (returns to practice phase with same selectedSentence and clears feedback) and 'Done' (returns to result view). \n\nImplementation:\n1. Create `frontend/src/components/pronunciation/MissedWordDrill.tsx` — a self-contained component taking props `{ words: string[]; tts: ReturnType<typeof useSpeechSynthesis>; speech: ReturnType<typeof useSpeechRecognition>; onRetrySentence: () => void; onClose: () => void; }`. Internal state: `idx`, `attemptsForWord`, `results: ('correct'|'skipped')[]`, `phase: 'listen'|'record'|'feedback'|'summary'`. Use `useEffect` watching `speech.transcript` to auto-evaluate.\n2. Export it from `frontend/src/components/pronunciation/index.ts`.\n3. In `frontend/src/pages/Pronunciation.tsx`: add `const [missedDrillOpen, setMissedDrillOpen] = useState(false);`. In the shadowing-result render block (around the existing `feedback.word_feedback.some((w) => !w.is_correct)` Tips section), add a prominent button '🎯 Drill these words ({n})' that opens the drill (rendered as a section above the Comparison Playback or as an inline replacement of the result card while open). Wire `onRetrySentence` to reset `feedback`, `speech.reset()`, and `setShadowingState('listening')` then `tts.speak(selectedSentence)`.\n4. Add `frontend/src/__tests__/MissedWordDrill.test.tsx` covering: (a) renders progress and first word, (b) marks word correct when transcript matches (case-insensitive), (c) advances index after correct, (d) Skip advances and records 'skipped', (e) summary appears after last word and Retry callback fires.\n\nThis is frontend-only (no API, no DB, no migration), under 5 files, closes the practice loop directly on the page where the diagnosis happens, and reinforces speaking — the app's stated goal.",
