{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "MinimalPairs: add 'Speak the Pair' production mode with ASR contrast scoring",
  "description": "MinimalPairs currently only trains *listening* discrimination — users hear one of two contrasting words (e.g., light/right, base/vase) and pick which one. For Japanese learners, the *production* side of these contrasts (L/R, B/V, S/TH, etc.) is an even bigger fluency blocker. Add a new 'Speak the Pair' mode toggle on frontend/src/pages/MinimalPairs.tsx and a new component frontend/src/components/MinimalPairsSpeakMode.tsx that drills production:\n\nFlow per round (5 rounds/session, reusing pickRandomSet / startMinimalPairListening pool so no backend change is required):\n1. Show both words side by side with IPA and a 🔊 TTS button each (uses existing useSpeechSynthesis).\n2. The app randomly TARGETS one of the two words and asks the user to say it (e.g., 'Say: RIGHT (not light)').\n3. User taps mic → useSpeechRecognition (lang='en-US', continuous=false, interimResults=false) captures one utterance.\n4. Score the attempt: normalize transcript to lowercase letters; if it matches the target word → ✅ 'Clear contrast!'; if it matches the *other* word in the pair → ❌ 'Sounded like \"<other>\" — try again'; otherwise → ⚠️ 'Couldn't catch that, retry'. Allow up to 2 retries before auto-advance, tracking first-try success.\n5. After each round play TTS of BOTH words back-to-back at 0.85x so the user can hear the contrast they just produced.\n6. End-of-session results card: per-pair first-try accuracy, the contrast label (e.g., 'L vs R'), a 'Drill the misses' button that re-runs only failed pairs, and total stars (⭐ ≥80%, ⭐⭐ ≥90%, ⭐⭐⭐ 100%).\n\nUI integration: at the top of MinimalPairs add a segmented toggle [👂 Listen | 🎤 Speak] (default Listen, persist last choice in localStorage key 'mp_mode'). When Speak is selected, render <MinimalPairsSpeakMode contrast={contrast} pairs={rounds} onRestart={startSession} />. Reuse the existing contrast/round data (the round's word_a/word_b/ipa_a/ipa_b are sufficient — ignore the `play` field in speak mode).\n\nAccessibility: mic button has aria-label='Record pronunciation of <target word>', target word is announced via aria-live='polite', dark-mode colors use existing CSS vars (--bg-secondary, --text-primary, --success, --danger). Gracefully fall back with an inline banner 'Speech recognition not supported in this browser — switch to Listen mode' when useSpeechRecognition.supported is false.\n\nFiles: frontend/src/pages/MinimalPairs.tsx (add mode toggle + render branch + small CSS), frontend/src/components/MinimalPairsSpeakMode.tsx (new), frontend/src/utils/minimalPairs.ts (add small helper `scoreSpeakAttempt(transcript, target, other) -> 'match' | 'confused' | 'unclear'` — pure function, easy to unit test), tests/unit/test_minimal_pairs_speak.test.ts or extend tests/unit/test_minimal_pairs_utils.test.ts with cases for scoreSpeakAttempt (exact match, other-word confusion, empty transcript, punctuation/case insensitivity, partial-word substring like 'rights' counting as 'right'). No backend, no schema, no migration changes.",
