{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "Conversation Reply Hints — get 2-3 suggested replies when stuck",
  "description": "Add a 'Need a hint? 💡' button in the Conversation chat phase (frontend/src/pages/Conversation.tsx and/or its chat subcomponent under frontend/src/components/) that fetches 2-3 short, natural English reply suggestions tailored to the AI's most recent message. Each suggestion is rendered as a tappable chip — tapping inserts the text into the user's reply input (does NOT auto-send, so the learner still has to read it aloud / edit it). Optionally show a tiny 🇯🇵 toggle next to each chip to reveal a Japanese gloss inline (reuses the JP translation pattern from #650).\n\nWhy: Beginner/intermediate learners frequently freeze in free conversation. Today they can only retry, slow-replay, or give up. A lightweight hint nudges them past the blocker without breaking the speaking-practice loop, directly supporting the app's fluency goal. Distinct from existing features: not a drill, not pronunciation feedback, not a translation of the AI line — it's *forward-looking reply scaffolding*.\n\nBackend: add POST /api/conversation/{conversation_id}/reply-hints in app/routers/conversation.py. Body: {turn_index?: int}. Behavior:\n- Load the conversation row and topic via conv_dal (reuse existing helpers; do NOT add columns — no migration needed).\n- Take the last assistant message (or message at turn_index if provided) plus the topic label.\n- Call the Copilot service via safe_llm_call with a new prompt key 'conversation_reply_hints' (added to config.yaml prompts section if a prompt registry exists, otherwise inline) instructing the model to return STRICT JSON: {\"hints\": [{\"en\": str, \"jp\": str}, ...]} with exactly 3 short (≤10 word) natural learner-level replies that move the conversation forward. Parse defensively; on parse failure return 200 with hints=[] and a 'fallback' flag so the UI can hide the panel quietly.\n- Apply require_rate_limit dependency, mirror error handling style of other endpoints in this router.\n- Cache the last response per (conversation_id, turn_index) in-memory for ~60s to avoid duplicate LLM spend if the user toggles the panel.\n\nFrontend: add api.ts function fetchReplyHints(conversationId, turnIndex?). Add a small collapsible HintsPanel component (or inline in Conversation chat component) with: button '💡 Hint', loading spinner, 2-3 chips, and a per-chip 'JP' toggle. Clicking a chip calls the existing setInput / message-input setter. Track usage with the existing metrics hook (e.g. trackEvent('conversation_hint_used')) if present; otherwise skip silently. Hide the button entirely if the last message is from the user (no AI turn to respond to).\n\nTesting: add a unit test in tests/unit/ for the new endpoint covering (a) happy path returns 3 hints, (b) malformed LLM JSON returns hints=[] with fallback flag, (c) 404 when conversation_id missing. Mock copilot_service like other conversation tests do.\n\nFiles to modify (≤5): backend router, api.ts, one Conversation component, one new test file, and config.yaml ONLY if a prompts: section already holds conversation prompts (otherwise inline the prompt in conversation.py to stay within the no-config-change rule).",
