{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "Quick Thought-Group Phrasing Card (chunk-the-sentence drill)",
  "description": "Add a new Quick Practice card 'QuickThoughtGroupCard' that trains learners to perceive and produce English thought groups (sense groups / prosodic phrasing) — a known bottleneck for fluency that current cards don't target. Cards like QuickConnectedSpeechCard focus on word-level liaison and QuickSentenceStressCard focuses on prominence; nothing yet trains *where to pause*.\n\nFlow:\n1. LISTEN phase: Backend returns one longer-than-average sentence (15-25 words, intermediate/advanced) plus an array of correct pause indices (word indices where a thought-group boundary belongs). TTS plays the sentence in full at normal speed.\n2. CHUNK phase: Sentence is rendered as tappable word chips. User taps between words to insert a '|' pause marker. Show count 'X / Y pauses placed'. A 'Hear chunked' button plays the sentence with short SSML-like pauses (implemented client-side by splitting sentence into segments and calling speak() sequentially with 250ms gaps between chunks at the user's chosen positions).\n3. CHECK: 'Reveal' button colors each gap green (correct), red (wrong place), gray (missed). Show precision/recall and a one-line tip referencing the rule (e.g., 'Pause before subordinate clauses (because/when/if)', 'Pause after long subjects', 'Pause at commas').\n4. SHADOW phase: User taps mic, shadows the sentence trying to honor the correct pauses. Use existing useSpeechRecognition; score = word-level transcript similarity (reuse normalize+token-overlap helper from QuickShadowCard). Award a small bonus if recording duration is within ±15% of the chunked playback duration (proxy for honoring pauses).\n5. Persist best F1 score for pause placement in localStorage ('thought-group-best-f1') and show a Trophy badge when beaten.\n\nBackend (app/routers/listening.py + app/prompts.py):\n- New endpoint `GET /api/listening/thought-group?difficulty=` returning `{ sentence: str, words: [str], pause_indices: [int], rules: [str] }` where pause_indices are 1-based positions meaning 'pause AFTER word i'. Use LLM via copilot_client with a prompt asking for one natural sentence and the indices of its thought-group boundaries plus a short rule label per boundary. Validate indices are within range and unique; fall back to a small static bank of 8 hand-curated sentences if LLM call fails or returns invalid JSON.\n- No DB schema changes, no migrations needed.\n\nFrontend:\n- Add `getThoughtGroup` to `frontend/src/api.ts` with TS types `ThoughtGroupResponse`.\n- New `frontend/src/components/QuickThoughtGroupCard.tsx` following the visual conventions of QuickConnectedSpeechCard (header icon, phase-driven UI, dark-mode classes, mobile-friendly chip layout via flex-wrap).\n- Register the card in `QuickPracticeHub.tsx` (add to the cards array with icon Scissors or Pause from lucide-react, label 'Thought Groups', short description 'Hear a sentence, tap where to pause, then shadow it').\n\nWhy this matters: pausing at the wrong places is one of the most intelligibility-damaging habits of L2 speakers; targeted perception+production practice on phrasing yields measurable fluency gains and is currently absent from the app.",
  "files_to_modify": [
    "app/routers/listening.py",
    "app/prompts.py",
    "frontend/src/api.ts",
    "frontend/src/components/QuickThoughtGroupCard.tsx",
    "frontend/src/components/QuickPracticeHub.tsx"
  ],
  "test_plan": "1. Backend unit test in tests/ for the new endpoint: mock copilot_client to return a valid JSON payload and assert response shape, indices in range, deduped; mock a malformed LLM response and assert fallback bank is used. 2. Manual: open Quick Practice → Thought Groups → verify Listen plays, tapping toggles pauses, 'Hear chunked' produces audibly segmented playback, Reveal colors gaps correctly, mic shadow scores and persists best F1 to localStorage. 3. Verify dark mode and mobile (375px) layouts render without overflow. 4. npm run build and pytest must pass.",
  "acceptance_criteria": "- New GET /api/listening/thought-group endpoint returns valid payload (LLM or fallback) with 200 in <2s. - QuickThoughtGroupCard renders in QuickPracticeHub and supports the full Listen → Chunk → Check → Shadow flow. - Pause precision/recall and shadow similarity are shown to the user. - Best F1 persists across reloads. - Works in dark mode and at 375px width. - All existing tests still pass; new backend test for the endpoint passes."
}
