  "description": "On the Listening Quiz page (frontend/src/pages/Listening.tsx), when the user answers a question incorrectly, currently they only see the explanation and must move on to the next question — the only way to re-hear the relevant sentence at slow speed is via the post-quiz Review screen (replayReviewSentence at 0.75×). Add an inline drill loop so the user can immediately repair their listening gap before continuing.\n\nChanges:\n1. After `handleAnswer` runs and the chosen option is wrong (`answered === true && selectedOption !== q.correct_index`), render a new compact panel inside the quiz card that shows: the relevant passage sentence (via `findRelevantSentenceIndex(q.question, q.options[q.correct_index], sentences)`) and two buttons: 'Listen slowly' (plays sentence at 0.75×) and 'Listen normal' (plays at 1.0×). Reuse a small inline player akin to `replayReviewSentence` but local to the quiz phase — set a new state `inlineReplayPlaying: boolean` and use Volume2 / Play icons from lucide-react already imported.\n2. Add a per-user toggle (persisted in localStorage key `listening.autoReplayOnWrong`, default false) labeled 'Auto-replay slowly on wrong' that lives next to the existing Speed Ladder toggle in the quiz toolbar. When true, the slow replay starts automatically (one time) as soon as a wrong answer is registered. Cancel any ongoing utterance via `window.speechSynthesis.cancel()` first so it composes safely with existing playback state.\n3. Do not count these inline replays toward `replayCounts` or flip `firstListenFlags`, since the question is already answered and we don't want to penalize listening-stat metrics.\n4. Hide the panel when `selectedOption === q.correct_index` (correct answers don't need repair) and when moving to the next question (cleanup in `handleNext`).\n\nWhy: This creates a tight 'hear-it-now' repair loop right at the moment of error — better encoding than waiting until the post-quiz review — and supports the app's mission of efficient short listening practice. It is fully frontend-only (no API/schema changes), reuses existing helpers (`findRelevantSentenceIndex`, `extractSentences`, `SpeechSynthesisUtterance`), and is easily testable.\n\nTests: extend `frontend/src/__tests__/Listening.test.tsx` (or create one) with a small unit for a new pure helper `shouldShowInlineReplay({ answered, selectedIndex, correctIndex }) => boolean`, and assert the panel renders only after a wrong answer in the quiz phase.",
